<br>
This will either get me laughed out of town or just maybe someone might think it a tad bit orginal. <br>
<br>
Okay here goes:  <br>
<br>
1)Wizards lament the lack of damage they deal within a given time frame in comparison to other classes. Warriors and Rogues comes to mind. <br>
<br>
2) Some really bright wizards point out that the basic &quot;currency of battle&quot; for a melee class is HP's and those are readily maintainable\restorable in battle with the assistance of a good cleric. Basically, a warrior\rogue with a good cleric in the background can outdamage a wizard because wizzies spend a part of any given battle medding back the mana they burned. In stark contrast, as MANA consumers we are completely at a disadvantage vis-a-vis the melee's because our mana restoration rate (even with breeze, clarity, et al) pales in terms of its ability to allow us to deliver the damage needed to keep up with a Rogue or Warrior, for example. This is old news as you all know. I only bring it up to pair it with the #1 item because I think it leads naturally to a possible suggestion to make to VI. <br>
<br>
Suggestion:<br>
<br>
A new spell called Hermetic Transformation whereby a wizard can cast it upon themselves before entering into the meditative state. It would increase the mana regen per tick proportional to some loss in the wizards HP total. Kind of a twisted sort of Lifetap for mana deal. <br>
<br>
Help me with this people.....make your own suggestions. But consider this before poo pooing the whole concept......for VI to nix this outright we could justifiably ask what the purpose of permitting melees engaged in combat to be healed? Why shouldn't the battered Rogue who has been backstabbing for a 1K damage per pop be required to DISENGAGE the enemy before the heal would take effect. Same goes for the Warrior. Make them assume the sitting position, away from battle, before the heal could take place. Not too much to ask of a melee class....wizards do it all the time. It's the only way we get to restore our capabilty to deal damage. <br>
<br>
I would ask VI to forget for a moment, every complaint made about damage in terms of numerical information or resistances or what have you.....just focus on this principle. Does any player, irrespective of class, deserve to have their damage dealing ability restored while still engaged with the enemy while another class cannot? <br>
<br>
I'm okay with my little ole Ice Comet(no need to mess with mana costs, etc) if the battered Warrior has to join me in the sitting position as he gets healed and I enter a hermetic transformed enhanced meditation state. Then the cleric can pop me a heal and we'll both return to battle on an possibly more equitable footing......<br>
<br>
Just an idea......<br>
<br>
Goanad <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualeolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aleolin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/27/01 9:06:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Agree</span><hr size=1> There are fungi tunics that replinish Hp. Why aren't there tunics that replace mana? Seems only fair.<br>
