- Swedish Chef</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoanad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goanad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/01 11:55:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We need Hermetic Transformation</span><hr size=1> There are some good followup posts. <br>
<br>
I guess at the end of the brainstorming day should be a consensus arrived upon, first by the Wizzies themselves, and then hopefully by whatever powers at VI who would listen, to the extent that we can agree on the following:<br>
<br>
1) Game dynamics proceed from certain principles that VI themselves establish. For example, they want ALL classes to be drawn to grouping versus soloing. Moreover, successful groups are groups where classes understand their roles and know enough about situations in the game to truly be a good addition to their groups. <br>
<br>
2) Arrive at the empirical reality, testable via surveying or other data collection methods, that Wizards have become less attractive to groups who want to administer the most damage to mobs and thereby increase the EXP gain for members the most. <br>
<br>
3) Flowing from #2, simply delve into WHY Rogues are more attractive now, and then, contrast that with Wizards. <br>
<br>
<br>
I just cannot comprehend how there could not be a consensus reachable by people here on this board and VI. BUT, and it's a big BUTT(pardon the pun), IF certain ppl's at VI have an axe to grind against the class as a whole, then it may be difficult to even &quot;get them to the table,&quot; so to speak. Then the worst fears of the pessismist on this board will come to pass and all Wizards to come will pay for whatever Wizards of the past have done to so alienate VI. In such an event what VI should do is simply eliminate the class. Why punish Wizards of the future by saddling them with a class which has been rendered &quot;non-group&quot; friendly? Save them their time, and make the game fun for everyone by directing players to classes which are better balanced. <br>
<br>
My 1 coppers worth!~<br>
<br>
Goanad <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bryek>Bryek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/01 1:12:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hermetic transformation == lich</span><hr size=1> Check out the lich series that necros get in the game.  You just stepped on the necro's toes.  Absor would be horrified<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
